26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_i2c_g94.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:34 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "priv.h"
30#include "pad.h"
31
32void
33g94_aux_stat(struct nvkm_i2c *i2c, u32 *hi, u32 *lo, u32 *rq, u32 *tx)
34{
35 struct nvkm_device *device = i2c->subdev.device;
36 u32 intr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00e06c);
37 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00e068) & intr, i;
38 for (i = 0, *hi = *lo = *rq = *tx = 0; i < 8; i++) {
39 if ((stat & (1 << (i * 4)))) *hi |= 1 << i;
40 if ((stat & (2 << (i * 4)))) *lo |= 1 << i;
41 if ((stat & (4 << (i * 4)))) *rq |= 1 << i;
42 if ((stat & (8 << (i * 4)))) *tx |= 1 << i;
43 }
44 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x00e06c, intr);
45}
46
47void
48g94_aux_mask(struct nvkm_i2c *i2c, u32 type, u32 mask, u32 data)
49{
50 struct nvkm_device *device = i2c->subdev.device;
51 u32 temp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00e068), i;
52 for (i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
53 if (mask & (1 << i)) {
54 if (!(data & (1 << i))) {
55 temp &= ~(type << (i * 4));
56 continue;
57 }
58 temp |= type << (i * 4);
59 }
60 }
61 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x00e068, temp);
62}
63
64static const struct nvkm_i2c_func
65g94_i2c = {
66 .pad_x_new = g94_i2c_pad_x_new,
67 .pad_s_new = g94_i2c_pad_s_new,
68 .aux = 4,
69 .aux_stat = g94_aux_stat,
70 .aux_mask = g94_aux_mask,
71};
72
73int
74g94_i2c_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_i2c **pi2c)
75{
76 return nvkm_i2c_new_(&g94_i2c, device, index, pi2c);
77}
